# Festag Mobile UI (Portal, ≤768px)

Every client portal subpage shares the same mobile chrome. Do not invent per-page header or footer patterns.

## Top left — page header

- Large Aeonik title, left-aligned (e.g. „Gesamtbericht“, „Entscheidungen“, „Projekte“).
- Match existing pages: `MobileCodexListChrome` (`.mcl-head`), decisions mobile (`.dec-m-head`), or `DashboardMobileStart` (`.dms-head`).
- Optional subtitle below title; no duplicate mobile headers.

## Top right — search + menu (always together)

- Use **`CodexMobileActionPill`** — one white pill with **both** Suche and Menü.
- **Suche** → `window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('open-command-palette'))`
- **Menü** → open **`MobileNavSheet`** (`setNavOpen(true)`).
- Never show search alone. Never replace the pill with separate orbs. Never hijack Menü for scope/period pickers.

## Bottom — exactly two page actions

- Use **`MobilePageDock`**: white sheet, **drag grip** (`.mpd-grip`) on top, then **two** buttons.
- **Primary** (left): wide ghost pill — main action for *this* page (e.g. „Statusbericht erstellen“, „Neues Projekt“).
- **Secondary** (right): round filled CTA — second action for *this* page (e.g. Play, Tagro, Filter).
- Labels/icons change per route; the **two-button dock pattern does not**.

Special case **`/dashboard`**: teleprompter center + sheet rows; dock uses same `mpd-*` tokens inline in `DashboardMobileStart`.

## Do not

- Add a persistent 5-tab bottom nav (Status / Post / Entsch. / Mehr / Tagro) or mount `PortalMobileDock` in `PortalAppShell`.
- Remove the drag handle or collapse the dock into a bare input bar.
- Hide `.mpd-grip`, menu button, or second dock button on portal pages.
- Replace `MobilePageDock` with a global nav bar.

## Preferred wiring

```tsx
<CodexMobileActionPill
  onSearch={() => window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('open-command-palette'))}
  onMenu={() => setNavOpen(true)}
/>
<MobileNavSheet open={navOpen} onClose={() => setNavOpen(false)} />
<MobilePageDock onDragUp={...} primary={...} secondary={...} />
```

List pages: wrap in **`MobileCodexListChrome`**. Custom layouts must still use the same three primitives.

Every portal subpage using `dec-os` / `dec-m-shell` **must** mount **`MobilePageDock`** — including Führung, Vorfälle, Aktivität, Anbindungen, Lieferungen, Team, etc. Missing dock is a regression.
